question:
District category contains Automotive District, Historic Neighborhood, Archaeological District, and Senior Living Community.
Supermarkets category contains Wegmans, 99 Cents Only Stores, Lulu Hypermarket, and Big Lots.
The number of each Historic Neighborhood 's 99 Cents Only Stores equals 4 times each Automotive District 's 99 Cents Only Stores.
The number of each Automotive District 's Lulu Hypermarket equals 14.
The number of each Archaeological District 's 99 Cents Only Stores equals 15.
The number of each Historic Neighborhood 's Lulu Hypermarket equals 21.
The number of each Automotive District 's Wegmans equals 1.
The number of each Senior Living Community 's Lulu Hypermarket equals each Archaeological District 's Wegmans.
The number of each Historic Neighborhood 's Big Lots equals 5 times the difference of each Historic Neighborhood 's Lulu Hypermarket and each Automotive District 's Wegmans.
The number of each Automotive District 's 99 Cents Only Stores equals 19.
The number of each Archaeological District 's Wegmans equals 3 more than each Historic Neighborhood 's 99 Cents Only Stores.
How many Supermarkets does Senior Living Community have?
solution:
Define each Automotive District 's 99 Cents Only Stores as j; So j = 19.
Define each Historic Neighborhood 's 99 Cents Only Stores as f; So f = 4 * j = 4 * 19 = 7.
Define each Archaeological District 's Wegmans as h; So h = 3 + f = 3 + 7 = 10.
Define each Senior Living Community 's Lulu Hypermarket as W; So W = h = 10.
Define each Senior Living Community 's Supermarkets as i; So i = W = 10.
